Global Wrapping Tissue Market Insights
Wrapping Tissue Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Wrapping Tissue Market Overview
The global wrapping tissue market is valued at USD 5.24 billion in 2024 and is projected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 4.2% from 2024 to 2032. The market is primarily driven by the increasing demand for eco-friendly and biodegradable packaging solutions. Key sectors, such as retail, cosmetics, and food industries, are rapidly adopting wrapping tissue as a sustainable alternative to conventional plastic packaging. The consumer shift towards sustainable packaging and growing environmental concerns have further bolstered the growth of this market.

Wrapping tissue is widely used for wrapping gifts, food items, and luxury products. As the need for sustainable packaging solutions intensifies globally, manufacturers are focusing on producing wrapping tissues from recycled materials, ensuring eco-friendliness while meeting consumer demands for aesthetics and functionality. As per market research, North America and Europe hold significant market shares, while Asia-Pacific is expected to witness rapid growth in the coming years.

